            <p>
                There are three types of hajj: Ifrad, Qiran and Tamattu.
            </p>
            <p><b>Hajj Ifrad:</b> Hajj only, without ‘umrah.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>A person performing Ifrad Hajj is called Mufrid</li>
                <li>In this type of Hajj, Mufrid enter into Ihram with an intention to perform Hajj only</li>
            </ul>

            <p><b>Hajj Qiran:</b>‘Umrah and Hajj with a single Ihram</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li>One who performs Qiran is called a Qarin</li>
                <li>In Qiran Hajj, Qaarin enters into Ihram with an intention to perform ‘umrah and Hajj together, without any break in between</li>
                <li>Some scholars rule that for this type of Hajj,  it is a prerequisite for the pilgrim (Qaarin) to have the sacrificial animal with them</li>
            </ul>
            <p><b>Hajj Tamattu:</b>‘Umrah and Hajj with a break in between (involves two separate Ihrams)</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:square">
                <li>The performer of this Hajj is called a Mutamatti</li>
                <li>In this type of Hajj, the pilgrims enter into Ihram with an intention to perform ‘umrah first, and then complete all ‘umrah rites with one Ihram before starting of Hajj</li>
                <li>Thereafter, before leaving for Mina on or before 8th Dhul-hijja , the pilgrims (Mutamatti) enter into Ihram again with an intention to perform Hajj only and complete all Hajj rites</li>
            </ul>


