            <h3>Which type of Hajj is the best?</h3>
            <p>There is disagreement among scholars about this. Some hold opinion that Tammattu is better while others think it is Ifrad. A third group of scholars are in favour of Qiran.</p>
            <p>The Prophet (peace be upon him) did perform Qiran Hajj, however, he recommended his companions to do Tammattu. When the Prophet (peace and blessings be upon him) arrived in Makkah and did the Tawaf on arrival, he told his companions to complete their `’umrah and release themselves from ihram. They wondered at that and questioned him, specially as they saw that he himself did not do what he told them to do. The Prophet (pbuh) replied and said: “You know that I fear Allah the most, and that I am the most truthful, and the most pious amongst you. If I had not brought my sacrificial animals with me, I also would have terminated my state of Ihram. If I were to come (to Makkah) again, I shall not bring the sacrificial animals with me. So terminate your state of Ihram.” The companions listened and obeyed the Prophet (pbuh). (Sahih Al-Bukhari 26:713) </p>

